AngloGold Plans to Invest $310 Million in Colombia by 2013, Republica Says

-- B y   H e l e n   M u r p h y
-- 
2011-05-19T23:28:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/anglogold-plans-to-invest-310-million-in-colombia-by-2013-republica-says.html
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG) , the world’s
third-largest gold miner, plans to invest $310 million in
 Colombia  by 2013, daily La Republica reported.  This year the company has budgeted $110 million in the
Andean nation, the daily reported, citing Rafael Herz, president
of AngloGold’s Colombian unit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helen Murphy in Bogota at 
 hmurphy1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jonathan Roeder at 
 jroeder@bloomberg.net  